S. Korea Regulator Says Rapid Capital Outflow a Major Concern

-- B y   S e o n j i n   C h a
-- 
2011-09-21T23:33:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/s-korea-regulator-says-rapid-capital-outflow-a-major-concern.html
The potential outflow of foreign
capital from  South Korea  is a major concern amid global economic
woes, Financial Services Commission Chairman Kim Seok Dong said.
The current global economic difficulties will likely drag on for
a “quite long” period, Kim said today in a CBS radio interview
in  Seoul .  To contact the reporter on this story:
